OL,3,CMinisters seek public's views on
OL,4,Ccouncil carve-up
OL,6,FThe government announced last month
OL,7,Fthat two unitary authorities would be
OL,8,Fcreated in Surrey to replace the
OL,9,Fcurrent 12 councils.
OL,11,FThe District Councils' Network
OL,12,Fwelcomed the starting of public
OL,13,Fconsultations and said it "firmly
OL,14,Fexpects local people to endorse
OL,15,Fproposals to keep councils close to
OL,16,Fcommunities, rather than impose mega
OL,17,Fcouncils".
